result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:57 PM Defendant Eric Joseph Jensen in court.  Attorney Michael Charles Hoffman in court for Eric Joseph Jensen.  Attorney Angela Wilson appeared in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case.  State cites agreement that defendant will plead to count 1 in 21CF477 without repeater with a joint recommendation of 1 year imposed and stayed for 3 years probation, condition of probation is 13 days jail with 13 credit, time served, DOC programming and $50 fine plus costs.  22CF48 will be dismissed but read in. Defendant will plead to 22TR465. and fine of $200.50 inclusive will be imposed with 3 points.  Defendant and attorney Hoffman agree.
Defendant pleads no contest to citation. Court orders fine of 200.50 inclusive.
in 12CF477 Court recounts charges and possible penalties. Defendant pleads no contest. Court informs defendant of rights given up by his plea. Defendant understands. Stipulation to factual basis. Court finds defendant understands proceedings and waives rights knowingly, freely and voluntarily.  Court accepts plea and finds that plea is freely and knowingly made. Court finds defendant guilty and judgment of conviction is entered. All other charges dismissed but read in.

records.addlTxt: No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription.  No operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant has valid permit or license.

01:40 PM Defendant Eric Joseph Jensen in court with attorney Ellen Denise Craker.  Defendant Eric Joseph Jensen in custody.  Chad C La Lor appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Eric Joseph Jensen appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant's address confirmed.  Attorney/defendant acknowledges receipt of criminal complaint, waives reading, enter not guilty in misdemeanors. Court accepts plea of not guilty on the misdemeanor counts.  States request on bail: $750 cash bail with conditions of  No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription, No operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant has valid permit or license. State indicates defendant is currently on probation in 21CF477. State gives further prior criminal history with OAR/OWI cases. 
Atty Craker argues against bail. Defendant is currently represented by Atty Hoffman. Defendant is out on Signature Bond on the 21CF477 case and has made all Court appearances. Defendant has been at the address over a decade. Defendant would like to address the Court. Defendant is supposed to attend treatment tomorrow. Defendant indicates he has been good about reporting to Court.
Court indicates there is a serious history and failing to report to jail and failure to appear to court. There are muliple bail-jumping charges. Court Orders $1000 cash bail with conditions of No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription.  No operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant has valid permit or license. 
Defendant does qualify for PD.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for February 23, 2022 at 10:30 am.
